oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Morris-Jumel mansion
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the Morris- Jumel Mansion which shows the exterior of the building showing the Palladian architecture and Tuscan columns.
Served as Washington's headquarters during the American Revolution. Built for Roger Morris and Mary Phillipse Morris. Bought by Stephen Jumel in 1810. Later renovated in the Federal style.
